Context / what landed:
PR-9 closes two EU-5f-surfaced robustness items.
(1) Concurrent-embed safety. PRE-FLIGHT FINDING (HITL-reviewed): running the real CandleBgeEmbedder (BertModel::forward is itself all-core multi-threaded) concurrently on the 2 projection workers does NOT wedge or corrupt, but oversubscribes CPU and collapses throughput ~13x (~0.27 vs ~3.6 docs/s). FIX (HITL-approved option a): serialize embeds engine-side via a `embed_serialize: Mutex<()>` guard held by the worker across the embed; commit/IO stays parallel. PROJECTION_WORKERS stays 2. A configurable per-embedder concurrency knob (Invariant 4) is explicitly deferred (out of PR-9 scope).
(2) Embed watchdog (ADR Invariant 5). embed_with_watchdog runs each embed on a detached thread with recv_timeout(default 30s, configurable via set_embed_timeout_ms_for_test); on timeout returns RuntimeEmbedderError::Timeout which the existing retry/failure path at run_projection_job already handles. Cancellation is "finish + discard" per Invariant 5 (no thread-abort). It is panic-transparent: embed panics are caught on the watchdog thread and resume_unwind'd on the worker thread so the EU-5f catch_unwind still records ProjectionPanic.

Focus the review on:
1. The serialization guard does not regress throughput beyond intent and the per-row cost is acceptable; commit/IO genuinely stays parallel (guard released before commit).
2. The watchdog cannot false-timeout a legitimately-slow-but-under-budget cold embed.
3. Serialization + watchdog COEXIST safely: when an embed times out while the worker holds embed_serialize, there is no lock-poisoning and no pool deadlock (the worker releases the guard on timeout; the abandoned detached embed thread runs lock-free; a panic-poisoned guard is recovered via into_inner).
4. Single-writer + projection-cursor freshness contracts are preserved (the guard/watchdog only wrap the embed, not the commit).
5. Test quality: the RED->GREEN framing is honest (serialization test asserts peak in-flight == 1; watchdog test asserts drain returns + no corruption + no false-timeout).

