**What passed on inspection**
- The prior blocker is closed. Spawn decisions are serialized under `embed_serialize`, and the breaker now keys off `live_embed_threads` before each spawn, so timed-out threads accumulate toward the threshold whether hangs are persistent or intermittent. That bounds live abandoned watchdog threads for both cases. Refs: [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3518), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3603), [pr9_embed_watchdog.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/pr9_embed_watchdog.rs:300).
- The increment/decrement accounting is correct on the reviewed panic path. `live_embed_threads` increments before spawn; the watchdog thread always runs `fetch_sub` after `tx.send`, including when `embed()` panics and the caller later `resume_unwind`s. The decrement is in the spawned thread, so caller unwind does not skip it. Refs: [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3531), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3544), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3424).
- I do not see a race that defeats the bound. The only concurrent mutation outside the guard is thread completion decrementing the live count; that can at worst make a worker observe a stale high count and latch early, not stale low in a way that permits overspawning past the intended cap. Fast-fail checks at entry and per retry remain intact. Refs: [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3557), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3576), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3611).
- Single-writer, cursor freshness, and panic handling remain intact. The new guard only wraps embed execution; commits still happen later under the separate `commit_gate`, and worker-level `catch_unwind` still converts panics into `ProjectionPanic` outcomes plus state cleanup. Refs: [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3507), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3430), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3962).
- The serialization rationale is now aligned with the evidence: safety-first, throughput-neutral on candle, and the long-seed comments no longer overclaim old behavior. Refs: [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:185), [pr9_embed_serialization.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/pr9_embed_serialization.rs:1), [pr9_concurrent_embed.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/pr9_concurrent_embed.rs:1).

